title: High Energy Neutral Atom (HENA) H Images, Key Parameters, IMAGE - Dr. Don Mitchell (APL)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/image/hena/hena_k0/2000/im_k0_hena_20000421_v01.cdf. The most common cadence, 119997 [ms] = PT1M59.997S, occurred for 15.9879% of the 106 timesteps.

parameters.name: Image0_V
parameters.description: ENA H Images @ 50-60 keV (no grid, small format, linear scale) - Image0. This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function crop_image (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['Image0']. Note that some COMPONENTS may not be available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.
